==English==

===Etymology===
It is originally from [[Boston]], when the [[baked beans]] that had just come out of the oven were cool enough to eat, the cook would announce, “Cool Beans.” It became more popular as a result of a Bush Beans commercial in the mid 1980s, when the talking dog, Duke, said it in one of their commercials

===Interjection===
'''[[cool]] [[beans]]'''
# [[okay]]
